QUESTION NO: 4
When you are selling the value proposition of the IOC you should explain the seen and unseen
value of the IOC solution.
What is a good example of unseen value?
A. The IOC has a guaranteed standard support L1, L2, L3 structure; custom solutions suffer from
knowledge decay within the organization over time
B. The IOC can be accessed via mobile devices.
C. If the IOC is not exactly what your customer needs, you can access and use the applications
that make up the IOC
D. The IOC can be hosted on a PC
Answer: B
Reference:http://www-01.ibm.com/support/docview.wss?uid=swg27036248&aid=1(page 24, see
installing the mobile application on a mobile device)
